1
00:00:01,175 --> 00:00:02,306
BOYD:
Previously on
From.

2
00:00:03,090 --> 00:00:05,092
[GROANING]
[BONES CRACKLING]

3
00:00:06,397 --> 00:00:08,921
We need to figure out
where you're going to live
from now on.

4
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:10,880
I don't think
she's a bad person.

5
00:00:10,967 --> 00:00:13,578
If it's all right, she would
like to live here with you.

6
00:00:13,665 --> 00:00:14,840
Okay, sure.

7
00:00:16,103 --> 00:00:18,931
[GUNSHOTS]
[SCREAMING]

8
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:21,369
Abby, stop! No! Stop!

9
00:00:21,456 --> 00:00:22,544
[GASPS]

10
00:00:22,674 --> 00:00:24,981
Hey, Abbs.
I could really use some help.

11
00:00:26,026 --> 00:00:27,853
No! Hey, hey! Hey, hey!
[GROANS]

12
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:30,813
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

13
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:33,294
Elgin, I don't want to hate you.

14
00:00:33,381 --> 00:00:35,426
This place took advantage
of both of us.

15
00:00:36,079 --> 00:00:38,081
There's something
I need your help with.

16
00:00:38,168 --> 00:00:40,388
I think we're gonna need
a little bit more.

17
00:00:40,475 --> 00:00:43,260
So you just... walk inside?

18
00:00:43,347 --> 00:00:44,870
Then I find my dad.

19
00:00:44,957 --> 00:00:46,524
Ethan called it Storywalking.

20
00:00:46,611 --> 00:00:48,004
He learned about it
from one of his books,

21
00:00:48,091 --> 00:00:49,397
and all his books
are under the house now.

22
00:00:49,571 --> 00:00:50,615
Shit!

23
00:00:51,268 --> 00:00:52,443
I see the bag.

24
00:00:52,530 --> 00:00:53,836
What are the titles?

25
00:00:53,923 --> 00:00:56,099
Grand Gooligog, the Cromenockle.

26
00:00:56,186 --> 00:00:57,709
Jade, tell me you got something.

27
00:00:58,406 --> 00:01:00,669
The best thing I can do
is just find a way to unlock

28
00:01:00,756 --> 00:01:02,584
whatever's locked in here.

29
00:01:02,671 --> 00:01:05,500
Henry said Miranda
started seeing this place

30
00:01:05,587 --> 00:01:07,067
after an acid trip they took.

31
00:01:07,719 --> 00:01:10,157
If it worked for her,
it stands to reason
it could work for me.

32
00:01:11,593 --> 00:01:14,335
The night we arrived here,
you had a dream.

33
00:01:14,422 --> 00:01:15,510
Lake of Tears?

34
00:01:15,597 --> 00:01:17,642
It's here,
and I need you to find it.

35
00:01:18,208 --> 00:01:20,080
VICTOR: Maybe Jade can help.
Jade?

36
00:01:20,167 --> 00:01:21,472
The lake of what?

37
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:23,387
ETHAN: Why were you meditating?

38
00:01:23,474 --> 00:01:25,172
Trying to remember something
that I used to know.

39
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:27,913
JADE: Hey, Victor,
we got a lake to find.

40
00:01:31,047 --> 00:01:32,222
ETHAN: Victor!

41
00:01:32,788 --> 00:01:34,398
Hey, talk to me, son.

42
00:01:35,269 --> 00:01:37,097
I told myself it wasn't real.

43
00:01:37,184 --> 00:01:38,924
I told myself it wasn't real.

44
00:01:43,451 --> 00:01:45,757
My wife, Miranda,

45
00:01:45,844 --> 00:01:49,761
she painted things she saw here.

46
00:01:50,327 --> 00:01:53,113
One of those paintings
was of a man in a yellow suit.

47
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:57,204
You're telling me
this could be the same suit?

48
00:01:57,291 --> 00:01:59,684
You don't see a lot of people
walking around here

49
00:01:59,771 --> 00:02:00,990
in a canary yellow suit.

50
00:02:01,077 --> 00:02:02,948
Well, Victor obviously
recognized it.

51
00:02:03,035 --> 00:02:05,864
He didn't just recognize it.
I watched a grown man
wet his pants.

52
00:02:05,951 --> 00:02:08,606
My question is,
if the suit's here, then...

53
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,652
where's the guy who wore it?

54
00:02:10,739 --> 00:02:12,610
Long gone, maybe.

55
00:02:12,828 --> 00:02:15,439
For all we know, this suit
might have been laying out
in the forest for years.

56
00:02:15,526 --> 00:02:18,138
This close to town?
Look, it's not like
it's easy to miss.

57
00:02:18,225 --> 00:02:19,922
Then maybe those things
that come out at night

58
00:02:20,009 --> 00:02:21,837
left it there
to mess with our heads.

59
00:02:21,924 --> 00:02:23,708
The point is, we don't know.

60
00:02:24,274 --> 00:02:26,537
The best thing we can do
right now is talk to Victor.

61
00:02:26,624 --> 00:02:28,583
I'll do it. I'll talk to him.
No, maybe we should all.

62
00:02:28,670 --> 00:02:29,758
I...

63
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:34,154
I will talk to my son alone.

64
00:02:36,243 --> 00:02:37,244
Okay.

65
00:02:37,679 --> 00:02:39,942
If there's nothing else, I'll...
BOYD: Yeah, no, okay.

66
00:02:43,424 --> 00:02:46,427
The young boy,
the one dressed in white,

67
00:02:46,514 --> 00:02:50,387
he said to us that
we're running out of time.

68
00:02:50,996 --> 00:02:53,042
For 40 years,

69
00:02:53,129 --> 00:02:56,915
that boy was nothing
but a painting in my basement.

70
00:02:57,002 --> 00:02:59,309
That suit, this place,

71
00:02:59,396 --> 00:03:02,182
all just paintings
in the basement. And now...

72
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,928
I think there was a part of me
that was still trying to pretend

73
00:03:10,015 --> 00:03:11,495
any of this was normal.

74
00:03:20,069 --> 00:03:21,113
Does he know?

75
00:03:21,723 --> 00:03:22,854
About his wife?

76
00:03:24,247 --> 00:03:25,335
About you?

77
00:03:27,511 --> 00:03:28,730
We don't even know if it's real.

78
00:03:29,731 --> 00:03:30,775
It's real.

79
00:03:30,862 --> 00:03:32,864
BOYD: No. No, Tabitha's right.

80
00:03:33,474 --> 00:03:35,519
We need to be
pretty goddamn sure.

81
00:03:36,390 --> 00:03:37,826
Have you said
anything to Fatima?

82
00:03:37,913 --> 00:03:39,567
No, she's dealing
with enough as is.

83
00:03:39,654 --> 00:03:42,309
All right, then everyone who
knows is standing in this room.

84
00:03:42,396 --> 00:03:44,136
Let's keep it that way for now.

85
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,225
Understood?

86
00:03:46,269 --> 00:03:47,923
JADE:
The man in the yellow suit...

87
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:51,013
If Miranda was able
to paint him,

88
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:53,885
that means somewhere
in your mind, there might be
an answer to who he is.

89
00:03:53,972 --> 00:03:57,280
If this is about
your fucking mushrooms...
[EXHALES]

90
00:03:57,367 --> 00:04:00,805
Boyd, are you seriously okay
with him taking magic mushrooms

91
00:04:00,892 --> 00:04:03,286
that he found
in a haunted forest?

92
00:04:03,373 --> 00:04:05,027
No, Donna, I'm not.

93
00:04:05,941 --> 00:04:07,856
I'm also not okay
with waking up every morning

94
00:04:07,943 --> 00:04:09,945
and counting how many
new bodies there are.

95
00:04:10,032 --> 00:04:11,468
Are you okay with that?

96
00:04:11,555 --> 00:04:13,383
We're losing, okay?

97
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:16,473
I'm not gonna say that
out there, but in here...

98
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,953
whatever game this is...

99
00:04:18,736 --> 00:04:20,042
we are losing.

100
00:04:20,564 --> 00:04:23,350
And then that freaky
little kid in white pops up

101
00:04:23,437 --> 00:04:25,308
and tells Tabitha
that we're running out of time,

102
00:04:25,395 --> 00:04:27,615
and we still don't know
the goddamn rules.

103
00:04:30,618 --> 00:04:33,273
If there are answers
in his head, any answers,

104
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:35,362
we need to get them out. Okay?

105
00:04:36,711 --> 00:04:37,886
I'll be there with him.

106
00:04:37,973 --> 00:04:40,236
Anything goes wrong,
I'm right there.

107
00:04:40,323 --> 00:04:41,759
Well, good luck with that.

108
00:04:42,325 --> 00:04:45,633
Ellis, there are people waiting
to go up to the settlement
to gather food.

109
00:04:46,764 --> 00:04:48,549
People still need to eat.

110
00:04:49,550 --> 00:04:53,902
And you, you do this,
you go on this little trip,

111
00:04:55,382 --> 00:04:57,253
you know you may not
come back, right?

112
00:04:58,776 --> 00:04:59,821
Yeah.

113
00:05:02,389 --> 00:05:03,781
Come on, let's go.

114
00:05:03,868 --> 00:05:04,826
Yeah.

115
00:05:10,484 --> 00:05:14,183
Boyd, would you mind
giving us a minute, please?

116
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:18,318
What? Yeah, of course. Yeah.

117
00:05:28,545 --> 00:05:29,633
[KNOCKING]

118
00:05:32,462 --> 00:05:33,507
Come in.

119
00:05:36,814 --> 00:05:38,163
I hope I didn't wake you.

120
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:39,904
I didn't sleep much.

121
00:05:40,644 --> 00:05:42,385
Neither did I at first.

122
00:05:43,778 --> 00:05:44,953
I, um...

123
00:05:46,084 --> 00:05:49,349
I was hoping we could talk.

124
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:50,959
Okay.

125
00:05:59,402 --> 00:06:01,970
I assume Kenny
told you about me?

126
00:06:03,275 --> 00:06:05,103
About what I did?
Yeah.

127
00:06:09,194 --> 00:06:10,805
So why would you want
to live here?

128
00:06:11,675 --> 00:06:13,590
Because when I met you,
I knew you were kind.

129
00:06:14,896 --> 00:06:17,028
I know what you did
was terrible, but...

130
00:06:17,115 --> 00:06:19,640
my father used to always say
that only good people

131
00:06:19,727 --> 00:06:21,859
are tortured by the bad things
that they've done.

132
00:06:23,426 --> 00:06:25,646
Plus, I figured
here I get my own room.

133
00:06:25,733 --> 00:06:26,908
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

134
00:06:29,432 --> 00:06:31,086
I'll go make us breakfast.

135
00:06:31,913 --> 00:06:33,088
I'll be right down.

136
00:06:48,669 --> 00:06:51,193
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

137
00:06:56,720 --> 00:07:00,202
[MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

138
00:07:07,601 --> 00:07:08,602
Ow.

139
00:07:09,254 --> 00:07:10,386
[GROANS]

140
00:07:11,039 --> 00:07:12,083
Ow!

141
00:07:12,170 --> 00:07:14,390
[CRIES] No, no, no, no.

142
00:07:14,477 --> 00:07:16,436
No, no, please!

143
00:07:16,523 --> 00:07:19,656
[YELPS] No, no, no, no, please!
Sara?

144
00:07:20,396 --> 00:07:21,745
[SCREAMS]
What's wrong?

145
00:07:22,877 --> 00:07:24,139
[SCREAMS]

146
00:07:25,706 --> 00:07:29,361
["QUE SERA, SERA [WHATEVER
WILL BE, WILL BE]" PLAYS]

147
00:07:35,629 --> 00:07:40,460
♪ When I was just a little boy

148
00:07:40,547 --> 00:07:42,897
♪ I asked my father ♪

149
00:07:42,984 --> 00:07:44,942
♪ "What will I be?" ♪

150
00:07:46,683 --> 00:07:49,033
♪ "Will I be handsome?"

151
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,079
♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪

152
00:07:51,558 --> 00:07:54,430
♪ Here's what he said to me ♪

153
00:07:55,605 --> 00:07:58,478
♪ Que sera, sera

154
00:07:59,696 --> 00:08:03,395
♪ Whatever will be, will be

155
00:08:04,614 --> 00:08:08,139
♪ The future's not ours to see

156
00:08:09,227 --> 00:08:11,839
♪ Que sera, sera

157
00:08:13,841 --> 00:08:17,018
♪ What will be will be

158
00:08:26,157 --> 00:08:31,032
♪ Now I have
children of my own ♪

159
00:08:31,119 --> 00:08:33,425
♪ They ask their father ♪

160
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:35,515
♪ "What will I be?" ♪

161
00:08:37,212 --> 00:08:39,649
♪ "Will I be pretty?"

162
00:08:39,736 --> 00:08:42,086
♪ "Will I be rich?" ♪

163
00:08:42,173 --> 00:08:45,307
♪ I tell them tenderly ♪

164
00:08:46,177 --> 00:08:49,050
♪ Que sera, sera

165
00:08:50,268 --> 00:08:53,794
♪ Whatever will be, will be

166
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:58,581
♪ The future's not ours to see

167
00:08:59,713 --> 00:09:02,498
♪ Que sera, sera

168
00:09:04,369 --> 00:09:07,547
♪ What will be, will be

169
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:12,508
♪ Que sera, sera

170
00:09:22,039 --> 00:09:23,650
[SONG CONCLUDES]

171
00:09:26,914 --> 00:09:28,002
[DOOR CLOSES]

172
00:09:28,089 --> 00:09:29,612
Why were you
in the woods with Ethan?

173
00:09:31,048 --> 00:09:33,442
You should really
ask Ethan about that.
I'm asking you.

174
00:09:33,529 --> 00:09:34,835
[SIGHS]

175
00:09:35,792 --> 00:09:37,489
Did he tell you
he saw Jim in the forest?

176
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,710
Yeah.

177
00:09:41,450 --> 00:09:44,279
Apparently, Jim told him
that he had to find
the Lake of Tears.

178
00:09:44,366 --> 00:09:46,063
Does that sound familiar?

179
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:47,282
That's not real.

180
00:09:47,369 --> 00:09:48,457
No, it's not.

181
00:09:48,892 --> 00:09:50,198
But it is to him.

182
00:09:50,807 --> 00:09:53,375
I'm not exactly the best person
to be giving advice about...

183
00:09:55,856 --> 00:09:57,684
Well, anything, really.

184
00:09:57,771 --> 00:10:01,209
But I do know some kids
just feel more comfortable

185
00:10:01,296 --> 00:10:02,602
living in their imagination.

186
00:10:03,646 --> 00:10:06,040
Right? It's where they go
when the world gets scary.

187
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:10,348
Because sometimes
believing in impossible things,

188
00:10:10,435 --> 00:10:13,482
it helps with the...

189
00:10:15,745 --> 00:10:16,703
It just helps.

190
00:10:23,231 --> 00:10:25,363
I'm sorry about
what I said in the barn.

191
00:10:27,061 --> 00:10:28,192
Don't be.

192
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:31,718
You weren't wrong.

193
00:10:38,594 --> 00:10:39,987
Be careful with those.

194
00:10:43,381 --> 00:10:45,557
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

195
00:10:47,429 --> 00:10:48,778
Everything all right?

196
00:10:49,474 --> 00:10:51,346
If you can tell me the last time
everything was all right,

197
00:10:51,433 --> 00:10:52,521
you win a cookie.

198
00:10:52,608 --> 00:10:54,131
Okay, you ready for this?

199
00:10:57,134 --> 00:10:58,222
Fuck no.

200
00:11:04,402 --> 00:11:05,447
Ethan?

201
00:11:17,111 --> 00:11:18,112
Dad?

202
00:11:19,156 --> 00:11:20,462
Can you hear me?

203
00:11:22,116 --> 00:11:23,900
Please. Answer me.

204
00:11:24,031 --> 00:11:25,162
Dad?

205
00:11:28,035 --> 00:11:29,036
Yeah?

206
00:11:39,046 --> 00:11:41,178
[SIGHS]

207
00:11:43,485 --> 00:11:45,705
Why didn't you tell me
about the Lake of Tears?

208
00:11:48,185 --> 00:11:50,927
Why did you go to Jade
and Victor and not come to me?

209
00:11:52,581 --> 00:11:56,193
Ethan, I need you
to talk to me, please.

210
00:12:03,287 --> 00:12:05,812
I didn't tell you because
I knew you wouldn't believe me.

211
00:12:10,294 --> 00:12:11,948
He told me I need to find it.

212
00:12:13,558 --> 00:12:14,734
He told me.

213
00:12:16,997 --> 00:12:20,217
And when I find it,
that'll prove it was real.

214
00:12:23,003 --> 00:12:24,221
He's not gone.

215
00:12:25,309 --> 00:12:26,876
He's still here.

216
00:12:35,972 --> 00:12:37,408
Okay, then.

217
00:12:37,495 --> 00:12:38,888
I need you to pack a bag.

218
00:12:40,672 --> 00:12:42,500
Why?
We're going on a trip.

219
00:12:54,904 --> 00:12:57,472
You find anything?
No, they're kids' books, Julie.

220
00:12:57,559 --> 00:12:59,604
If you don't wanna help me,
I can do this on my own.

221
00:12:59,691 --> 00:13:00,997
I'm not saying that.

222
00:13:01,084 --> 00:13:02,129
I just...

223
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:07,264
Hm.

224
00:13:07,961 --> 00:13:09,223
What?

225
00:13:10,180 --> 00:13:11,268
Storywalker Fred.

226
00:13:13,749 --> 00:13:14,750
Who?

227
00:13:15,925 --> 00:13:16,970
Who's that?

228
00:13:17,057 --> 00:13:18,623
Yeah, he's the...

229
00:13:19,624 --> 00:13:21,452
distant cousin
of the Grand Gooligog.

230
00:13:21,539 --> 00:13:23,063
Uh, here we are.

231
00:13:23,411 --> 00:13:26,109
"Storywalker Fred
was an elevator repairman
who spent his weekends

232
00:13:26,196 --> 00:13:28,372
Storywalking as he pleased
through all the wondrous tales

233
00:13:28,459 --> 00:13:29,939
and greatest adventures
of our time."

234
00:13:31,723 --> 00:13:33,160
TABITHA: Julie?

235
00:13:33,247 --> 00:13:34,248
Hide the books.

236
00:13:34,988 --> 00:13:36,685
Uh, yeah, we're in here.

237
00:13:41,821 --> 00:13:43,126
I need you to pack your bag.

238
00:13:43,213 --> 00:13:44,388
We're going out
to the settlement.

239
00:13:45,389 --> 00:13:46,477
Why?

240
00:13:46,869 --> 00:13:48,828
Ethan's convinced he needs
to find the Lake of Tears.

241
00:13:50,264 --> 00:13:52,570
The magic lake
he used to talk about?

242
00:13:52,657 --> 00:13:53,658
Yeah.

243
00:13:54,616 --> 00:13:55,878
He said he saw your father,

244
00:13:55,965 --> 00:13:57,967
and then your dad
asked him to find it.

245
00:13:59,403 --> 00:14:00,840
S-- He saw him?

246
00:14:00,927 --> 00:14:02,624
What-- What does that mean?

247
00:14:02,711 --> 00:14:03,843
I don't know.

248
00:14:04,756 --> 00:14:05,801
I think he's grieving.

249
00:14:07,759 --> 00:14:09,979
What I do know
is that if I try to stop him,

250
00:14:10,066 --> 00:14:12,982
then he'll sneak out
and look for it by himself.

251
00:14:14,331 --> 00:14:16,072
This way I can keep him safe.

252
00:14:18,509 --> 00:14:19,554
Okay.

253
00:14:20,598 --> 00:14:22,035
So what do you need me for?

254
00:14:22,774 --> 00:14:24,472
Well, you're not
staying here alone.

255
00:14:24,559 --> 00:14:27,083
I'm not going to be alone.
I'll be with Randall.

256
00:14:27,170 --> 00:14:28,171
Randall.

257
00:14:28,302 --> 00:14:31,218
Mom, it's not like that.
It's really not.

258
00:14:32,784 --> 00:14:35,265
I'll stay at the clinic.
Kristi and Marielle are there.

259
00:14:37,702 --> 00:14:39,095
Can I talk to you for a minute?

260
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:41,837
JULIE: Mom.
It's okay.

261
00:14:43,795 --> 00:14:44,927
[RANDALL SIGHS]

262
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:55,285
First of all,
I just want to say sorry.
No, no, no. Stop talking.

263
00:14:55,372 --> 00:14:56,983
Just listen.
Okay.

264
00:14:57,592 --> 00:14:59,289
I don't know you, Randall.

265
00:14:59,376 --> 00:15:01,335
I don't know who you are
or what you want.

266
00:15:01,422 --> 00:15:02,597
Julie trusts you.

267
00:15:03,076 --> 00:15:05,774
She feels safe around you,
and she needs that right now.

268
00:15:05,861 --> 00:15:08,081
So I need you to look me
in the eye and tell me

269
00:15:08,168 --> 00:15:10,561
you understand
what I will do to you

270
00:15:10,648 --> 00:15:12,520
if you ever do anything
to break that trust.

271
00:15:13,956 --> 00:15:15,088
I understand.

272
00:15:16,089 --> 00:15:17,177
Okay, good.

273
00:15:19,135 --> 00:15:20,093
Mom.

274
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:21,181
Honey.

275
00:15:22,095 --> 00:15:23,052
What?

276
00:15:24,706 --> 00:15:26,838
I love you.
I love you too.

277
00:15:28,057 --> 00:15:30,059
Promise me you'll be okay.
Promise.

278
00:15:30,146 --> 00:15:31,321
Yeah.

279
00:15:33,584 --> 00:15:35,151
I'll be back tomorrow.

280
00:15:35,238 --> 00:15:36,239
Yeah.

281
00:15:38,459 --> 00:15:39,895
This is your water.

282
00:15:40,809 --> 00:15:43,377
I don't need to go.
[SIGHS] Ellis, it's your turn.

283
00:15:43,464 --> 00:15:45,988
Yeah, but I'm sure Donna can
find someone to take my place.

284
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:48,948
I'm fine.

285
00:15:49,557 --> 00:15:52,299
Donna needs people out there
that she knows she can rely on.

286
00:15:54,518 --> 00:15:56,694
Honey, I'm okay. I promise.

287
00:15:58,522 --> 00:15:59,523
Yeah.

288
00:16:00,698 --> 00:16:01,743
Okay.

289
00:16:02,787 --> 00:16:03,832
Okay.

290
00:16:06,052 --> 00:16:08,532
Tommy is responsible
for the cans on the door.

291
00:16:08,619 --> 00:16:10,926
Ella and Jordan
will check the windows.

292
00:16:11,013 --> 00:16:13,624
And then about 20 minutes
or so before sundown--

293
00:16:13,711 --> 00:16:16,540
Do a headcount.
I know. I got it.

294
00:16:16,627 --> 00:16:20,066
Just... keep an eye on Fatima,

295
00:16:20,675 --> 00:16:22,068
with Ellis gone.

296
00:16:22,155 --> 00:16:24,505
Yeah. I got it.
Yup.

297
00:16:24,592 --> 00:16:25,854
TABITHA: Donna?
Okay.

298
00:16:27,508 --> 00:16:29,118
Do you have room for two more?

299
00:16:30,163 --> 00:16:31,381
More the merrier.

300
00:16:35,777 --> 00:16:38,432
Okay. Let's, uh, move it out.

301
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:40,608
Come on.

302
00:16:42,131 --> 00:16:43,089
Let's go.

303
00:16:52,968 --> 00:16:55,405
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:12,596
[CHUCKLES] How's this?

305
00:17:12,683 --> 00:17:14,468
This is perfect.

306
00:17:14,555 --> 00:17:15,860
Thank you, Elgin.

307
00:17:16,078 --> 00:17:18,515
I can help you with the rest
if you tell me what this is for.

308
00:17:18,602 --> 00:17:20,300
The rest I have to do myself.

309
00:17:21,301 --> 00:17:22,650
You should go now.

310
00:17:23,825 --> 00:17:25,522
Uh, okay.

311
00:17:32,747 --> 00:17:37,360
One, two...
Victor, hey.

312
00:17:37,447 --> 00:17:40,102
...three, four...

313
00:17:40,711 --> 00:17:41,886
HENRY: What are you doing?

314
00:17:43,018 --> 00:17:44,976
I have to see
if the trees have moved.

315
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,631
Why-- Why would
the trees be moving?

316
00:17:47,718 --> 00:17:50,547
Because everything is changing,
and first it was snowing,

317
00:17:50,634 --> 00:17:51,983
and now everything's green,

318
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:53,637
and everything is just
moving too fast.

319
00:17:53,724 --> 00:17:55,639
And I used to measure
all the time,

320
00:17:55,726 --> 00:17:58,990
and then I haven't
been paying attention,

321
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:00,818
and I should have
been paying attention.

322
00:18:01,602 --> 00:18:03,343
I should have been
paying attention.

323
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:06,259
I should have...
[SNIFFLES]

324
00:18:10,176 --> 00:18:11,394
Can I help?

325
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:14,832
See if the trees are moving?

326
00:18:21,622 --> 00:18:22,666
Okay.

327
00:18:24,364 --> 00:18:26,366
Okay, uh, what do I do?

328
00:18:29,978 --> 00:18:32,894
You start with this leg
like this.

329
00:18:32,981 --> 00:18:34,156
One.

330
00:18:34,243 --> 00:18:35,244
One.

331
00:18:36,027 --> 00:18:37,203
Two.

332
00:18:39,466 --> 00:18:41,381
[WATER DRIPPING]

333
00:19:14,979 --> 00:19:16,677
What the fuck?

334
00:19:29,864 --> 00:19:30,952
Hi.

335
00:19:38,525 --> 00:19:40,309
[HUMMING]

336
00:19:52,756 --> 00:19:55,237
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:20:01,722 --> 00:20:03,637
BOYD:
You know what they used
to call me in the army, right?

338
00:20:03,724 --> 00:20:05,987
Mr. Fish and Loaves!
Mr. Fish and Loaves!
That's right.

339
00:20:35,364 --> 00:20:37,148
[HUMMING]

340
00:20:38,411 --> 00:20:39,368
Oh.

341
00:20:40,195 --> 00:20:41,196
Hi.

342
00:20:43,503 --> 00:20:44,591
Boyd?

343
00:20:45,374 --> 00:20:46,506
What's going on?

344
00:20:47,811 --> 00:20:50,597
Is Kenny in this room
right now?

345
00:20:51,162 --> 00:20:52,207
What?

346
00:20:53,469 --> 00:20:54,427
Yes.

347
00:20:55,123 --> 00:20:56,646
Never mind then.
[SIGHS]

348
00:20:57,995 --> 00:21:00,694
Is he on...
Mushrooms found in the woods.

349
00:21:02,130 --> 00:21:04,045
KENNY: Right.
You need something?

350
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:06,700
Uh, it's Fatima.

351
00:21:07,614 --> 00:21:09,572
I think maybe you should come up
to the Colony House.

352
00:21:21,367 --> 00:21:22,455
I should go.

353
00:21:22,542 --> 00:21:24,239
No. Stay.

354
00:21:26,807 --> 00:21:27,851
Please.

355
00:21:30,593 --> 00:21:31,594
Okay.

356
00:21:35,729 --> 00:21:37,644
You remember, this is
the first place I met you.

357
00:21:41,082 --> 00:21:42,257
It's funny how things change.

358
00:21:49,046 --> 00:21:50,352
Do you still see her?

359
00:21:50,439 --> 00:21:52,702
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

360
00:21:52,789 --> 00:21:54,835
The woman in the kimono?

361
00:21:56,140 --> 00:21:57,185
No.

362
00:21:58,404 --> 00:22:00,971
Do you think it's because
you did what she asked,

363
00:22:01,058 --> 00:22:02,799
so now she leaves you alone?

364
00:22:02,886 --> 00:22:06,325
Uh, Sara, is...
is something going on?

365
00:22:07,021 --> 00:22:08,065
[EXHALES]

366
00:22:09,980 --> 00:22:12,331
I thought for a while

367
00:22:13,375 --> 00:22:15,290
that the voices
were leaving me alone.

368
00:22:15,377 --> 00:22:18,206
I thought they were
done with me, but turns out...

369
00:22:19,381 --> 00:22:20,513
they're not.

370
00:22:22,471 --> 00:22:25,082
And what do they want you to do?

371
00:22:25,169 --> 00:22:26,519
It doesn't make any sense.

372
00:22:27,433 --> 00:22:29,826
They said they want me
to go to the diner,

373
00:22:30,436 --> 00:22:33,003
pour a glass of water
from the pitcher,

374
00:22:34,222 --> 00:22:37,094
take a sip,
and then pour it back in.

375
00:22:38,357 --> 00:22:39,532
And then what?

376
00:22:41,490 --> 00:22:42,491
That's it.

377
00:22:46,190 --> 00:22:48,584
So how... how is that
going to hurt anyone?

378
00:22:48,671 --> 00:22:49,716
I don't know.

379
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:53,459
But there's always
a consequence.

380
00:22:53,546 --> 00:22:54,938
Sara, it's just water.

381
00:22:56,549 --> 00:22:58,289
But I'll have drank from it.
So?

382
00:23:01,641 --> 00:23:06,602
Whatever is wrong with me,
what if it's like an infection?

383
00:23:08,430 --> 00:23:10,345
What if I pass it on
to someone else

384
00:23:10,432 --> 00:23:12,478
and then the voices
start torturing them?

385
00:23:12,565 --> 00:23:15,872
I don't want anyone
to have to live like this.

386
00:23:18,179 --> 00:23:19,180
Okay.

387
00:23:21,443 --> 00:23:23,053
What if you just don't do it?

388
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:25,360
They said if I don't
do it by midday,

389
00:23:25,447 --> 00:23:28,363
then something bad will happen
to someone that I care about.

390
00:23:29,364 --> 00:23:32,193
And it will keep happening
until I do it.

391
00:23:35,370 --> 00:23:37,503
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

392
00:23:41,985 --> 00:23:43,726
How many steps?

393
00:23:43,813 --> 00:23:45,859
Uh, 23.

394
00:23:52,735 --> 00:23:55,695
Victor, I want to talk to you
about what happened yesterday.

395
00:23:56,522 --> 00:23:58,001
Nothing happened yesterday.

396
00:23:58,611 --> 00:23:59,655
Can we...

397
00:23:59,742 --> 00:24:02,702
Dad, you can't just stop
in the middle,

398
00:24:03,354 --> 00:24:04,443
'cause you'll...

399
00:24:05,444 --> 00:24:06,836
You'll mess everything up.

400
00:24:07,358 --> 00:24:08,359
I'm sorry.

401
00:24:09,143 --> 00:24:11,841
But I need you to talk to me.

402
00:24:13,277 --> 00:24:14,888
Whatever it was,

403
00:24:15,584 --> 00:24:18,065
whatever you're afraid of,
you can tell me.

404
00:24:19,153 --> 00:24:22,286
Mm, so I... I think the tr--
I think they moved a little.

405
00:24:23,592 --> 00:24:27,291
You said that you told yourself
it wasn't real.

406
00:24:29,685 --> 00:24:31,644
Did you mean the yellow suit?

407
00:24:36,387 --> 00:24:38,912
Can you tell me
about the man who wore it?

408
00:24:38,999 --> 00:24:39,956
Did...

409
00:24:40,130 --> 00:24:42,829
Was he someone that hurt--
hurt you?

410
00:24:50,837 --> 00:24:52,795
Look, Victor, please.

411
00:24:54,667 --> 00:24:57,321
Whatever it is,
we'll face it together.

412
00:24:57,408 --> 00:24:58,627
You can tell me.

413
00:25:05,155 --> 00:25:08,245
Uh... Victor.
Wh-- Victor!

414
00:25:08,332 --> 00:25:10,683
Come-- Come with me
and I'll show you.

415
00:25:14,817 --> 00:25:18,299
Hey, just, uh, sit down
and don't go anywhere.

416
00:25:19,605 --> 00:25:20,823
Come on.

417
00:25:24,087 --> 00:25:25,088
[KNOCKING]

418
00:25:26,046 --> 00:25:27,177
Come in.

419
00:25:28,657 --> 00:25:30,616
[WATER SPLASHING]

420
00:25:32,792 --> 00:25:34,620
I told Kenny not to bother you.

421
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:37,666
Yeah.

422
00:25:39,581 --> 00:25:41,061
Well, he, uh...

423
00:25:45,369 --> 00:25:46,762
It's a lot of dirt.

424
00:25:47,415 --> 00:25:48,416
Yeah.

425
00:25:50,287 --> 00:25:51,724
You want to tell me
what's going on?

426
00:25:54,161 --> 00:25:55,423
I'm making a monster.

427
00:25:58,382 --> 00:25:59,383
JULIE: Here we go.

428
00:25:59,688 --> 00:26:01,995
The Grand Gooligog asks Fred
about Storywalking.

429
00:26:02,082 --> 00:26:04,475
"How do you choose a point
in the story you wish to see?"

430
00:26:04,563 --> 00:26:05,607
And?

431
00:26:06,129 --> 00:26:07,957
"Fred replied, 'you have
to create a bookmark.'"

432
00:26:08,523 --> 00:26:10,743
"Fred discovered that
by leaving a bookmark
somewhere in the story,

433
00:26:10,830 --> 00:26:13,006
he could choose whatever
chapter he wished to visit."

434
00:26:13,093 --> 00:26:14,050
[EXHALES]

435
00:26:14,137 --> 00:26:15,399
We have to make a bookmark.

436
00:26:16,792 --> 00:26:18,577
Julie, that doesn't
make any sense.
[SCOFFS]

437
00:26:18,664 --> 00:26:19,795
I know what you're gonna say.

438
00:26:19,882 --> 00:26:22,319
This is a kid's book,
and it's crazy.

439
00:26:22,406 --> 00:26:23,407
It's because it is.

440
00:26:25,932 --> 00:26:27,716
What if that's not
the right way to look at this?

441
00:26:27,803 --> 00:26:30,110
What if Storywalking
existed here first?

442
00:26:30,197 --> 00:26:31,633
The fuck are you talking about?

443
00:26:32,112 --> 00:26:34,680
Everything here is impossible.

444
00:26:35,245 --> 00:26:36,507
Okay?

445
00:26:36,595 --> 00:26:37,900
But it's also real.

446
00:26:37,987 --> 00:26:40,511
We're here, right now,
in this impossible place.

447
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:43,993
What if all of the crazy shit
that happens here has been...

448
00:26:45,212 --> 00:26:47,910
like, seeping out into...

449
00:26:52,088 --> 00:26:53,481
My mom.

450
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,962
My mom had nightmares
about this place when
she was a little girl.

451
00:26:56,049 --> 00:26:58,660
She didn't realize that
she was dreaming about it then,
but she was.

452
00:26:58,747 --> 00:27:01,968
Okay? Who knows how many
other kids or adults

453
00:27:02,055 --> 00:27:04,666
or fucking children's book
authors have had dreams
about this place

454
00:27:04,753 --> 00:27:06,276
without knowing it.

455
00:27:06,363 --> 00:27:08,844
And what if this author
had a dream about
someone like me

456
00:27:08,931 --> 00:27:10,324
doing what I can do?

457
00:27:10,411 --> 00:27:12,718
He woke up, wrote it down,
and called it Storywalking.

458
00:27:13,283 --> 00:27:16,330
There's literally thousands
of books that have stories
and rules

459
00:27:16,417 --> 00:27:17,897
about traveling through time.
No. No.

460
00:27:17,984 --> 00:27:19,376
Why would this book...

461
00:27:20,029 --> 00:27:21,814
The one with fucking
Fred the Storywalker.

462
00:27:21,901 --> 00:27:23,685
Why would this book be the one
that explains anything?

463
00:27:23,859 --> 00:27:26,253
Because out of all
of those books, this is the one
my brother had with him

464
00:27:26,340 --> 00:27:28,124
when we came here. Okay?

465
00:27:29,038 --> 00:27:31,301
Well, maybe
that means something.
Mm-hmm.

466
00:27:31,388 --> 00:27:32,825
Maybe it's fate.

467
00:27:32,912 --> 00:27:34,565
I, uh--Fate?

468
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:35,828
Randall, if I'm right,

469
00:27:35,915 --> 00:27:38,004
this could actually
be an instruction manual

470
00:27:38,091 --> 00:27:39,570
on how to save my dad.

471
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:41,877
And it's all I have.

472
00:27:45,098 --> 00:27:46,708
So I'm going to try
whether you help me or not.

473
00:27:51,365 --> 00:27:53,367
So what kind of bookmark
do we need?

474
00:27:55,717 --> 00:27:57,371
BOYD: When you say monster...

475
00:27:57,458 --> 00:27:59,895
Boyd, I know
you're worried about me,

476
00:27:59,982 --> 00:28:01,636
but you don't have to be.

477
00:28:01,723 --> 00:28:03,986
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
I hear you saying that.

478
00:28:04,552 --> 00:28:06,249
The problem is,

479
00:28:06,336 --> 00:28:08,817
Fatima, this says
something else.

480
00:28:10,340 --> 00:28:12,516
Have you told Ellis
what you're doing in here?

481
00:28:13,430 --> 00:28:14,867
I wasn't trying
to hide it from him.

482
00:28:16,042 --> 00:28:18,697
He has been so worried lately.

483
00:28:19,436 --> 00:28:21,787
I figured once he was back
from the food run,

484
00:28:21,874 --> 00:28:23,527
once he could see
what I was doing,

485
00:28:23,614 --> 00:28:25,094
it would be easier to explain.

486
00:28:25,834 --> 00:28:26,966
Okay, great.

487
00:28:28,097 --> 00:28:29,446
Explain it to me?

488
00:28:36,410 --> 00:28:39,195
Where I grew up,
beliefs were very rigid.

489
00:28:40,893 --> 00:28:42,068
They defined you.

490
00:28:43,156 --> 00:28:45,898
But my dad told stories
of all the different faiths.

491
00:28:46,681 --> 00:28:48,770
He used to drive my mother crazy

492
00:28:48,857 --> 00:28:51,120
because she understood
how dangerous it was.

493
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:55,037
But he would just smile.
[CHUCKLES]

494
00:28:55,734 --> 00:28:59,999
He'd say, "Fatima,
they have it wrong."

495
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:03,263
"They all think their road
is the only way."

496
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:06,527
"Don't they understand that
all roads lead to the divine?"

497
00:29:07,223 --> 00:29:09,748
"They simply take
different paths to get there."

498
00:29:09,835 --> 00:29:11,053
Fatima.

499
00:29:11,140 --> 00:29:14,448
Of all the stories
my father would tell,

500
00:29:15,101 --> 00:29:17,407
all the fables and myths...

501
00:29:19,714 --> 00:29:22,935
there's one story I've been
thinking a lot about lately.

502
00:29:24,937 --> 00:29:26,939
Do you know
what a golem is, Boyd?

503
00:29:31,682 --> 00:29:32,858
[CLEARS THROAT]

504
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:35,817
[CLEARS THROAT]

505
00:29:40,691 --> 00:29:41,692
Well?

506
00:29:42,215 --> 00:29:43,477
She's, um...

507
00:29:46,828 --> 00:29:48,438
She's making a golem.

508
00:29:49,135 --> 00:29:50,092
A what?

509
00:29:50,963 --> 00:29:53,356
It's a part
of a religious folklore.

510
00:29:54,836 --> 00:29:57,143
It's a giant made of clay.

511
00:29:57,230 --> 00:29:59,101
It protects people.
It's a champion.

512
00:30:00,276 --> 00:30:02,844
She said it's a symbol of hope.

513
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:08,894
Maybe for now we just...
give her some space.

514
00:30:08,981 --> 00:30:11,070
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
That-- That's your solution?

515
00:30:12,941 --> 00:30:14,508
Give her some space?

516
00:30:14,595 --> 00:30:15,988
She's not hurting anybody.

517
00:30:16,075 --> 00:30:17,554
That's not the point.

518
00:30:17,641 --> 00:30:20,688
We have both seen
this place turn people,

519
00:30:20,775 --> 00:30:23,038
change them little by little
until one day...

520
00:30:23,734 --> 00:30:25,432
we turn around and...

521
00:30:27,651 --> 00:30:30,611
and the person that we knew
is-- is-- is gone.

522
00:30:32,308 --> 00:30:33,440
[BOYD SIGHS]

523
00:30:33,788 --> 00:30:37,618
Boyd, that person up there
is not the Fatima that I know.

524
00:30:38,793 --> 00:30:40,839
And I think if you're being
honest with yourself,

525
00:30:40,926 --> 00:30:42,797
that's not the Fatima
you know either.

526
00:30:44,625 --> 00:30:45,669
Mm.

527
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:54,287
DONNA: Can I ask you something?

528
00:30:55,114 --> 00:30:56,245
TABITHA: Yeah.

529
00:30:57,943 --> 00:30:59,596
What the hell
are you doing out here?

530
00:31:02,121 --> 00:31:03,122
I don't know.

531
00:31:05,167 --> 00:31:06,603
I don't know what I'm doing.

532
00:31:08,692 --> 00:31:12,044
I just keep walking around with
this knot of terror inside me

533
00:31:12,131 --> 00:31:13,915
that feels like
it's going to explode.

534
00:31:15,525 --> 00:31:17,049
And the whole time...

535
00:31:18,311 --> 00:31:21,662
there's this question
that keeps ringing in my mind.

536
00:31:24,360 --> 00:31:26,058
What am I supposed to do now?

537
00:31:27,189 --> 00:31:28,321
Jim's gone.

538
00:31:28,799 --> 00:31:30,801
I keep looking for him,
but he's gone.

539
00:31:34,109 --> 00:31:37,460
I have memories in my head
that belong to other people.

540
00:31:38,766 --> 00:31:41,116
Memories that
might have answers,

541
00:31:41,203 --> 00:31:45,120
but I'm terrified of what
it'll cost if I go too far,

542
00:31:45,207 --> 00:31:47,209
or if I remember too much.

543
00:31:49,124 --> 00:31:50,343
But if I don't...

544
00:31:59,047 --> 00:32:00,048
I know I'm failing.

545
00:32:01,658 --> 00:32:03,312
What's gonna happen
when Ethan learns

546
00:32:03,399 --> 00:32:06,446
that the Lake of Tears
is not real? [SIGHS]

547
00:32:08,056 --> 00:32:09,666
How am I gonna deal with that?

548
00:32:09,753 --> 00:32:10,841
DONNA: Hey, everyone.

549
00:32:11,668 --> 00:32:13,801
Let's just take
a little break, okay?

550
00:32:13,888 --> 00:32:15,063
You good?

551
00:32:15,150 --> 00:32:17,500
Yeah, we're fine.
Just need a little breather.

552
00:32:17,587 --> 00:32:18,545
Okay.

553
00:32:18,632 --> 00:32:19,807
Let's sit down.

554
00:32:30,513 --> 00:32:32,254
I don't know
how to do this alone.

555
00:32:32,341 --> 00:32:33,734
You are not alone.

556
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:38,043
People keep saying that.
Well, maybe you should
fucking listen.

557
00:32:38,130 --> 00:32:40,567
[EXHALES]
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

558
00:32:40,654 --> 00:32:42,961
I don't want to find
another one of those notes

559
00:32:43,048 --> 00:32:45,137
like the one on my nightstand.
Oh, Donna.

560
00:32:45,224 --> 00:32:46,921
You are not going to put me

561
00:32:47,008 --> 00:32:49,532
in the position of having
to explain to your kids

562
00:32:49,619 --> 00:32:51,665
why I'm still alive
and you're not.

563
00:32:51,752 --> 00:32:53,493
Donna, I'm--
No--

564
00:32:54,146 --> 00:32:59,455
You and those kids
are as much my family

565
00:32:59,542 --> 00:33:01,675
as any family I have ever had.

566
00:33:03,329 --> 00:33:04,765
So from now on...

567
00:33:06,419 --> 00:33:08,856
if anyone is going
to risk their lives

568
00:33:08,943 --> 00:33:10,989
to do something stupid...

569
00:33:11,902 --> 00:33:13,295
that person is gonna be me.

570
00:33:14,166 --> 00:33:15,776
[EXHALES]
And not you.

571
00:33:17,212 --> 00:33:18,561
[SNIFFLES]
We clear on that?

572
00:33:19,780 --> 00:33:21,608
I am asking,

573
00:33:21,695 --> 00:33:23,218
are we clear on that?
[CHUCKLES, SNIFFLES]

574
00:33:26,221 --> 00:33:27,222
We're clear.

575
00:33:27,309 --> 00:33:28,441
Okay.

576
00:33:28,963 --> 00:33:30,225
ETHAN: Mom!

577
00:33:30,312 --> 00:33:31,661
Come look at this!

578
00:33:33,359 --> 00:33:34,403
Come on.

579
00:33:41,889 --> 00:33:43,325
Looks like a broken wing.

580
00:33:44,631 --> 00:33:46,676
[CHIRPS]
Must have fallen
from a nest or something.

581
00:33:47,286 --> 00:33:49,027
We never see
anything here but crows.

582
00:33:49,984 --> 00:33:51,290
We have to take him with us.

583
00:33:51,986 --> 00:33:53,074
[CLEARS THROAT] Ethan.

584
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:57,339
Mom, this is a sign.

585
00:33:59,341 --> 00:34:02,562
If the lake at the settlement
really is the Lake of Tears,

586
00:34:02,649 --> 00:34:03,693
it'll fix him.

587
00:34:04,477 --> 00:34:05,652
That's how we'll know.

588
00:34:06,609 --> 00:34:08,046
We have to take him with us.

589
00:34:16,402 --> 00:34:18,708
I can't imagine
what this is like for her.

590
00:34:19,796 --> 00:34:22,538
At least when I got here,
I found you, you know?

591
00:34:23,626 --> 00:34:25,715
I mean, she lost
the only person she had here.

592
00:34:26,586 --> 00:34:27,630
Yeah.

593
00:34:28,936 --> 00:34:31,286
I can't tell
if she's handling it well or...

594
00:34:31,895 --> 00:34:33,245
just hasn't accepted it yet.

595
00:34:35,160 --> 00:34:36,857
She prays a lot.
Yes.

596
00:34:37,727 --> 00:34:38,989
I don't know, maybe it helps.

597
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:40,991
[CHUCKLES] Yeah, that's...

598
00:34:41,079 --> 00:34:42,428
[SMACKS LIPS]

599
00:34:42,906 --> 00:34:45,605
That was always
the one thing about NA
that I just couldn't stand.

600
00:34:45,692 --> 00:34:48,347
The whole giving yourself
up to a higher power.

601
00:34:48,434 --> 00:34:49,565
Mm.

602
00:34:50,044 --> 00:34:52,438
If there were ever proof that
no one's looking out for us,

603
00:34:52,525 --> 00:34:53,700
it's here.

604
00:35:02,143 --> 00:35:04,667
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

605
00:35:16,636 --> 00:35:17,985
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

606
00:35:23,425 --> 00:35:24,513
[EXHALES]

607
00:35:26,385 --> 00:35:27,777
[SIGHS]

608
00:35:27,864 --> 00:35:29,431
Hey.

609
00:35:29,518 --> 00:35:31,477
I don't see
a lot of you in here.

610
00:35:31,564 --> 00:35:33,435
I-- I-- I won't be long.

611
00:35:34,044 --> 00:35:36,395
Well, Sara, you can stay
as long as you like.

612
00:35:39,920 --> 00:35:42,923
I-- I think it's really nice
that you reopened the diner.

613
00:35:43,010 --> 00:35:45,926
Mm. Well, I thought it'd be
a good way to-- to keep busy.

614
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:48,189
You used to work here, right?

615
00:35:49,234 --> 00:35:51,714
Feels like a long time ago now.

616
00:35:51,801 --> 00:35:53,716
Well, if you ever
want to come back,

617
00:35:53,803 --> 00:35:55,022
I could use the help.

618
00:35:57,372 --> 00:36:00,680
Look, I wasn't here
when you did what you did.

619
00:36:01,463 --> 00:36:03,552
But who you've become
while I've known you...

620
00:36:04,858 --> 00:36:06,599
that girl deserves a place.

621
00:36:07,208 --> 00:36:08,383
Think about it.

622
00:36:13,562 --> 00:36:15,042
Bakta.
Yeah?

623
00:36:18,263 --> 00:36:20,221
Do you mind
dumping that out for me?

624
00:36:20,308 --> 00:36:21,483
Oh.

625
00:36:21,570 --> 00:36:22,658
Sure.

626
00:36:27,620 --> 00:36:29,752
[SOPHIA SCREAMS]
MARIELLE: Oh, shit.

627
00:36:29,839 --> 00:36:32,581
Wait, Marielle, what?
Marielle, wait!
What's happening?

628
00:36:33,539 --> 00:36:34,975
KRISTI:
I don't-- I don't know.

629
00:36:36,455 --> 00:36:38,413
I'm coming. Don't move, okay?

630
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:41,329
[WHIMPERING, GROANING]

631
00:36:41,938 --> 00:36:44,289
Stay right where you are.
Stay right where you are.

632
00:36:45,028 --> 00:36:46,726
Where does it hurt?
My arm.

633
00:36:46,813 --> 00:36:48,031
Okay. Let me see.

634
00:36:48,118 --> 00:36:50,338
Okay, look at me.
Take a deep breath.

635
00:36:50,425 --> 00:36:51,426
What happened?

636
00:36:52,340 --> 00:36:54,647
SOPHIA: I was standing
by the edge, and I felt like
something pushed me.

637
00:36:54,734 --> 00:36:56,257
[GASPING]

638
00:36:57,127 --> 00:36:58,738
MARIELLE:
Okay, is there anywhere else?

639
00:36:58,825 --> 00:37:00,043
SOPHIA: No.

640
00:37:01,306 --> 00:37:02,872
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

641
00:37:19,759 --> 00:37:21,239
[MUSIC FADES]

642
00:37:23,066 --> 00:37:25,112
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

643
00:37:31,510 --> 00:37:32,946
[CHATTERING IN DISTANCE]

644
00:37:33,033 --> 00:37:34,513
[DOOR OPENS]

645
00:37:35,818 --> 00:37:37,777
Hey, we done here?

646
00:37:39,822 --> 00:37:42,085
No. No, not quite.

647
00:37:45,785 --> 00:37:47,221
[EXHALES]

648
00:37:47,308 --> 00:37:49,267
Because Fatima's making
a mud monster?

649
00:37:51,486 --> 00:37:53,183
Sorry, I was eavesdropping.

650
00:37:56,970 --> 00:38:00,060
I don't know if I should
be up there stopping her...

651
00:38:00,930 --> 00:38:02,410
or if I should be
up there helping her.

652
00:38:06,980 --> 00:38:08,982
You know, if it wasn't for
what happened to me and Tabitha,

653
00:38:09,069 --> 00:38:10,505
everything we remembered,

654
00:38:11,506 --> 00:38:13,813
I never would have
even considered
taking those mushrooms.

655
00:38:16,511 --> 00:38:17,643
What's your point?

656
00:38:19,732 --> 00:38:21,037
My point...

657
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:23,692
is something changed.

658
00:38:25,215 --> 00:38:28,567
Made me realize
I had to do something drastic
before it was too late.

659
00:38:28,654 --> 00:38:31,265
Even if everyone around me
thought I was insane.

660
00:38:35,487 --> 00:38:37,358
So maybe the question
you need to ask Fatima

661
00:38:37,445 --> 00:38:40,405
isn't why
she's making that thing.

662
00:38:41,754 --> 00:38:42,929
[EXHALES]

663
00:38:43,712 --> 00:38:46,715
Maybe the question
you need to ask
is why she's making it now.

664
00:38:55,985 --> 00:38:57,335
Jesus.

665
00:38:59,772 --> 00:39:02,252
These things are
even creepier in person.

666
00:39:02,340 --> 00:39:04,733
Jade said they're
to ward off evil spirits.

667
00:39:05,430 --> 00:39:06,474
[CHUCKLES]

668
00:39:07,301 --> 00:39:08,607
Oh, that's, uh...

669
00:39:10,609 --> 00:39:12,132
comforting, I suppose.

670
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:15,004
Okay.

671
00:39:15,135 --> 00:39:17,006
The more food
we collect before dark,

672
00:39:17,093 --> 00:39:18,704
the earlier we leave
in the morning.

673
00:39:19,269 --> 00:39:21,446
So drop your bags. Let's go.

674
00:39:21,533 --> 00:39:23,883
Mom, we need
to get him to the lake.

675
00:39:24,884 --> 00:39:26,364
Come on. Let's go.

676
00:39:35,895 --> 00:39:37,070
Julie?

677
00:39:37,157 --> 00:39:38,463
JULIE: I'm up here.

678
00:39:39,507 --> 00:39:40,900
Got what you asked for.

679
00:39:45,078 --> 00:39:46,166
Got the--

680
00:39:47,602 --> 00:39:48,777
What are you doing?

681
00:39:48,864 --> 00:39:50,344
[SIGHS]
Last time I tried this,

682
00:39:50,431 --> 00:39:52,259
one of those things
grabbed me by the hair.

683
00:39:53,260 --> 00:39:54,914
That's not
going to happen again.

684
00:39:57,307 --> 00:39:58,961
[SIGHS]

685
00:39:59,048 --> 00:40:00,093
Okay.

686
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:02,008
Ready?

687
00:40:02,443 --> 00:40:03,444
Mm.

688
00:40:07,796 --> 00:40:10,669
Okay, so to create
a bookmark...

689
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:13,846
fold up a piece of paper

690
00:40:14,368 --> 00:40:16,370
and I bring it with me
when I Storywalk.

691
00:40:17,676 --> 00:40:20,287
Wherever I end up in the past,
like whatever chapter I'm in,

692
00:40:20,374 --> 00:40:23,725
I just draw the symbol...

693
00:40:24,596 --> 00:40:26,946
on the paper
and leave it there.

694
00:40:27,599 --> 00:40:29,296
If this works,
when you pull me out,

695
00:40:29,383 --> 00:40:30,776
the symbol that I drew
in the past

696
00:40:30,863 --> 00:40:33,039
will also be here on the paper
in the present.

697
00:40:39,262 --> 00:40:41,656
You've been waiting to do that
since we left town, haven't you?

698
00:40:41,743 --> 00:40:42,831
I have, yeah.

699
00:40:46,052 --> 00:40:47,053
Okay.

700
00:40:49,751 --> 00:40:51,231
Let's say this thing works.

701
00:40:51,797 --> 00:40:54,887
Let's say you make it
out of this thing
with a functioning bookmark.

702
00:40:54,974 --> 00:40:56,497
How does that help us?

703
00:40:56,584 --> 00:40:57,890
Because from that point forward,

704
00:40:57,977 --> 00:40:59,979
whatever point in the story
I want to visit,

705
00:41:00,066 --> 00:41:03,156
like the chapter right before
my father was killed...

706
00:41:05,375 --> 00:41:07,203
Write it here, in the folds,

707
00:41:07,290 --> 00:41:09,075
fold it back up,
cross the threshold.

708
00:41:10,163 --> 00:41:11,730
And that's where
the bookmark will take me.

709
00:41:11,817 --> 00:41:13,949
You're asking me to watch you
have another seizure.

710
00:41:15,603 --> 00:41:17,387
I'm asking you for five seconds.

711
00:41:19,302 --> 00:41:21,043
I draw the symbol,
you pull me out.

712
00:41:22,001 --> 00:41:24,351
Randall, if this works,
this changes everything.

713
00:41:26,571 --> 00:41:27,615
Please.

714
00:41:29,530 --> 00:41:30,488
Five seconds.

715
00:41:32,141 --> 00:41:33,229
Five seconds.

716
00:41:37,582 --> 00:41:40,280
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

717
00:41:41,890 --> 00:41:42,935
Come on.

718
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:44,589
Be careful.

719
00:41:47,853 --> 00:41:48,897
Yeah.

720
00:42:00,518 --> 00:42:02,171
[SHUDDERED BREATHING]

721
00:42:02,258 --> 00:42:04,522
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

722
00:42:06,349 --> 00:42:08,482
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

723
00:42:08,569 --> 00:42:10,789
[GRUNTING]

724
00:42:10,876 --> 00:42:13,095
[GASPING]

725
00:42:17,360 --> 00:42:19,841
[SQUELCHING]

726
00:42:23,497 --> 00:42:26,544
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

727
00:42:32,724 --> 00:42:33,899
[GASPING]

728
00:42:41,036 --> 00:42:43,430
[WHIMPERING]

729
00:42:43,517 --> 00:42:45,388
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Hey, hey, it's me.

730
00:42:45,475 --> 00:42:46,868
It's me. It's me.

731
00:42:46,999 --> 00:42:48,478
You're okay. You're okay.

732
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:49,697
You're okay.

733
00:42:52,526 --> 00:42:54,049
[SHUDDERED BREATHING]

734
00:42:54,136 --> 00:42:55,224
No.

735
00:42:57,444 --> 00:42:59,315
Fuck! [GROANS]

736
00:42:59,968 --> 00:43:02,405
It didn't work.
It didn't fucking work.

737
00:43:04,930 --> 00:43:06,888
[SHOVEL SCRAPING]

738
00:43:06,975 --> 00:43:09,587
[VICTOR PANTING]

739
00:43:12,502 --> 00:43:13,591
Victor, come on.

740
00:43:33,785 --> 00:43:35,264
VICTOR: They're in there.

741
00:43:57,417 --> 00:43:59,680
He came in a car
just like the rest of us.

742
00:44:00,855 --> 00:44:02,814
I thought his yellow suit
was funny.

743
00:44:03,597 --> 00:44:05,773
And we thought
he was just like us. We...

744
00:44:08,515 --> 00:44:11,561
brought him in
and made him our friend,

745
00:44:11,649 --> 00:44:13,215
but he wasn't like us.

746
00:44:13,912 --> 00:44:15,478
When everyone died,

747
00:44:16,088 --> 00:44:19,004
when I found Mom
out by The Bottle Tree,
I saw him.

748
00:44:22,660 --> 00:44:24,270
[GASPING]

749
00:44:24,357 --> 00:44:26,751
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

750
00:44:26,838 --> 00:44:28,187
He was eating her.

751
00:44:28,274 --> 00:44:30,842
Oh, God. Oh, God.

752
00:44:32,060 --> 00:44:33,496
[HENRY SOBBING]

753
00:44:36,586 --> 00:44:39,328
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

754
00:44:41,853 --> 00:44:43,811
KRISTI:
So it's definitely broken.

755
00:44:45,160 --> 00:44:47,597
But we're gonna wait
for the swelling to go down

756
00:44:47,685 --> 00:44:49,077
before we reset the bone.

757
00:44:49,164 --> 00:44:50,296
Okay.
Okay?

758
00:44:51,558 --> 00:44:53,516
I know all of this
is a little scary.

759
00:44:54,866 --> 00:44:56,345
It's just another test.

760
00:44:57,390 --> 00:44:58,608
It's why we're here.

761
00:44:59,131 --> 00:45:02,003
God is testing us
and allowing us
to prove our faith in him.

762
00:45:03,352 --> 00:45:04,397
Yeah...

763
00:45:06,007 --> 00:45:07,400
I know this all sounds
silly to you.

764
00:45:07,487 --> 00:45:08,967
No.

765
00:45:09,054 --> 00:45:11,360
No, it doesn't.
Do you know
the story of Abraham?

766
00:45:13,101 --> 00:45:15,451
Uh, no. No, I don't.

767
00:45:15,538 --> 00:45:16,583
Oh.

768
00:45:17,540 --> 00:45:19,760
He was a simple man
with an unshakable faith

769
00:45:19,847 --> 00:45:21,022
and obedience to God.

770
00:45:26,375 --> 00:45:29,291
One day, God tested Abraham,

771
00:45:29,378 --> 00:45:32,077
ordering him
to kill his only son

772
00:45:32,164 --> 00:45:33,948
as a way to prove his faith.

773
00:45:38,257 --> 00:45:39,954
But at the last moment,

774
00:45:40,041 --> 00:45:41,608
God intervened

775
00:45:41,695 --> 00:45:44,959
and offered a ram
to be sacrificed instead.

776
00:45:49,442 --> 00:45:54,752
You see, God never intended
for Abraham to kill his son.

777
00:45:57,929 --> 00:46:00,148
He simply needed
to know if he would.

778
00:46:00,279 --> 00:46:02,281
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

779
00:46:10,724 --> 00:46:12,030
[KNOCKING]

780
00:46:15,207 --> 00:46:17,775
Hey, okay if Kenny joins us?

781
00:46:28,046 --> 00:46:30,918
Look, I know how strange
this must seem, guys, but...

782
00:46:31,789 --> 00:46:34,966
Fatima, I need to know
why you're doing this.

783
00:46:35,053 --> 00:46:36,271
I told you
why I'm doing this.

784
00:46:36,358 --> 00:46:38,012
Why are you doing it now?

785
00:46:38,883 --> 00:46:41,407
Whatever it is,
I need you to tell me. Please.

786
00:46:41,494 --> 00:46:43,496
Don't-- Don't let this place
make you afraid to talk to me.

787
00:46:43,583 --> 00:46:44,758
I still feel it.

788
00:46:46,673 --> 00:46:47,717
S--

789
00:46:48,066 --> 00:46:50,285
That thing I carried inside me,
I still feel it.

790
00:46:51,112 --> 00:46:52,810
Okay.
Feel it how?

791
00:46:52,897 --> 00:46:53,898
Like we're connected.

792
00:46:55,116 --> 00:46:57,292
Part of me feels what he feels.

793
00:46:58,119 --> 00:46:59,164
Okay.

794
00:46:59,468 --> 00:47:01,601
And this thing that
you're making, it's gonna,

795
00:47:01,688 --> 00:47:03,037
what, break the connection?

796
00:47:03,124 --> 00:47:04,299
It goes both ways.

797
00:47:04,386 --> 00:47:05,518
Right.

798
00:47:05,605 --> 00:47:07,433
He feels what I'm feeling too.

799
00:47:08,129 --> 00:47:11,611
He feels how afraid I am.
He likes it.

800
00:47:12,786 --> 00:47:14,005
But making this...

801
00:47:15,441 --> 00:47:17,399
it makes me feel strong.

802
00:47:19,401 --> 00:47:22,274
It makes me feel less afraid.
Okay.

803
00:47:22,361 --> 00:47:24,232
It's the only way
I know to fight back.

804
00:47:25,364 --> 00:47:26,408
Right.

805
00:47:30,586 --> 00:47:31,631
Jesus.

806
00:47:32,414 --> 00:47:34,329
Making that thing,

807
00:47:34,416 --> 00:47:36,157
you think it could
actually help?

808
00:47:36,984 --> 00:47:39,900
I don't know.
But all things considered...

809
00:47:41,162 --> 00:47:43,338
having a champion in our corner,

810
00:47:43,425 --> 00:47:45,427
not the worst thing
in the world right now.

811
00:47:45,514 --> 00:47:47,473
I'll, uh, spread the word...

812
00:47:47,560 --> 00:47:49,388
Good....to give her some space.

813
00:47:49,867 --> 00:47:51,564
Keep everyone out of that room.
Yeah.

814
00:47:51,651 --> 00:47:52,739
Okay.

815
00:47:54,349 --> 00:47:55,394
[RING CLATTERS]

816
00:47:59,093 --> 00:48:01,704
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

817
00:48:25,076 --> 00:48:26,077
Boyd?

818
00:48:32,039 --> 00:48:33,519
We gotta go.

819
00:48:33,606 --> 00:48:34,737
Now.

820
00:48:37,523 --> 00:48:38,872
Boyd, what's wrong?

821
00:48:38,959 --> 00:48:40,265
Just give me a minute.

822
00:48:52,930 --> 00:48:55,802
[MUTTERING SOFTLY]

823
00:49:02,765 --> 00:49:03,853
What?

824
00:49:08,206 --> 00:49:09,250
No, it's...

825
00:49:12,253 --> 00:49:14,647
[MUSIC BUILDS]

826
00:49:25,397 --> 00:49:27,486
All right, new category.
[GRUNTS]

827
00:49:28,052 --> 00:49:29,531
Saturday morning cartoons.

828
00:49:29,618 --> 00:49:30,837
Okay, I'll go first.

829
00:49:31,969 --> 00:49:33,274
The Jetsons.

830
00:49:33,361 --> 00:49:34,710
PATTY: Ooh.

831
00:49:35,450 --> 00:49:36,712
The Flintstones.

832
00:49:36,799 --> 00:49:37,844
Nice.

833
00:49:39,759 --> 00:49:40,760
Okay.

834
00:49:45,199 --> 00:49:46,331
Ready?

835
00:49:46,896 --> 00:49:48,942
Okay. Let's do it.

836
00:49:56,950 --> 00:49:57,951
[CHIRPS]

837
00:50:04,262 --> 00:50:05,437
[GRUNTS]

838
00:50:05,524 --> 00:50:06,829
[SHOVEL CLATTERS]

839
00:50:12,966 --> 00:50:14,402
ELLIS: Roger, you good?

840
00:50:14,489 --> 00:50:15,838
What the fuck?

841
00:50:16,448 --> 00:50:18,928
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

842
00:50:21,105 --> 00:50:22,106
[CHIRPING]

843
00:50:28,895 --> 00:50:30,070
Mom?

844
00:50:32,594 --> 00:50:34,422
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

845
00:50:34,509 --> 00:50:35,684
Oh, fuck.

846
00:50:44,389 --> 00:50:46,739
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

847
00:51:26,431 --> 00:51:28,041
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]
